ZH: 这个无赖总是欺负小孩子。
EN: This scoundrel always bullies children.

ZH: 我真不明白为什么有那么多无赖在政府中工作。
EN: I really don't understand why there are so many scoundrels working in the government.

ZH: 这个商人是个彻头彻尾的无赖。
EN: This businessman is a complete scoundrel.

ZH: 他是一名无赖的律师，总是欺骗他的客户。
EN: He is a scoundrel lawyer who always deceives his clients.

ZH: 不要和那个无赖纠缠，他只会给你带来麻烦。
EN: Don't get involved with that scoundrel, he will only bring you trouble.

ZH: 这个无赖偷了我的钱包。
EN: This scoundrel stole my wallet.

ZH: 无赖们总是在夜里潜入别人的庭院。
EN: Scoundrels always sneak into other people's yards at night.

ZH: 这个无赖向我投掷了一颗石头。
EN: This scoundrel threw a stone at me.

ZH: 那个无赖总是对女性不敬。
EN: That scoundrel always disrespects women.

ZH: 我们必须抵制社会上的无赖行为。
EN: We must resist scoundrel behavior in society.

ZH: 这个无赖逃避了他应该承担的责任。
EN: This scoundrel evaded the responsibility he should have taken.

ZH: 我再也不想见到那个无赖了。
EN: I never want to see that scoundrel again.

ZH: 这个无赖连续三次偷走了我们的车。
EN: This scoundrel stole our car three times in a row.

ZH: 这个无赖欠了我一大笔钱，但却不还。
EN: This scoundrel owes me a large sum of money, but refuses to pay back.

